tation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span> is the maximum)</li>\n<li>The player who takes the last stone wins</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"markdown-h1\">The Question</h2>\n<p>For any values of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span> (starting stones) and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span> (maximum take), can you determine:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Whether the first player can guarantee a win?</li>\n<li>If so, what should their first move be?</li>\n</ol>\n<details class=\"hint-block\" data-type=\"hint\"><summary class=\"hint-label\">Hint</summary><div class=\"hint-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p>Think about the pattern you discovered in the basic version. How does it generalize?</p></div></details>\n<details class=\"hint-block\" data-type=\"hint\"><summary class=\"hint-label\">Modular Arithmetic</summary><div class=\"hint-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p>The key involves the remainder when dividing <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span> by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(k+1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</p></div></details>\n<details class=\"solution-block\" data-type=\"solution\"><summary class=\"solution-label\">Solution</summary><div class=\"solution-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p><strong>Answer</strong>: The first player can win if and only if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span> is not divisible by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(k+1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.</p><h3 class=\"markdown-h2\">The Winning Strategy</h3><p>Let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m = k + 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7778em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span> (one more than the maximum take).</p><p><strong>Winning positions</strong>: Any number of stones where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mtext> </mtext><mo lspace=\"0.22em\" rspace=\"0.22em\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mo><mtext> </mtext><mi>m</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\">≠</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n \\bmod m \\neq 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">mod</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mord vbox\"><span class=\"thinbox\"><span class=\"rlap\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"inner\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\"></span></span></span><span class=\"fix\"></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong>Losing positions</strong>: Any number of stones where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mtext> </mtext><mo lspace=\"0.22em\" rspace=\"0.22em\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mo><mtext> </mtext><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n \\bmod m = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">mod</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong>The Strategy</strong>:</p><ol>\n<li>If <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mtext> </mtext><mo lspace=\"0.22em\" rspace=\"0.22em\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mo><mtext> </mtext><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n \\bmod m = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">mod</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span>, you're in a losing position (your opponent can win with perfect play)</li>\n<li>If <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mtext> </mtext><mo lspace=\"0.22em\" rspace=\"0.22em\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mo><mtext> </mtext><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n \\bmod m = r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">mod</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span> (where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0 &#x3C; r \\leq k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6835em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span>), take <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span> stones to leave a multiple of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span> for your opponent</li>\n<li>After each opponent move, always take enough stones to keep the total removed equal to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol><h3 class=\"markdown-h2\">Why This Works</h3><p>When you leave a multiple of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span> stones:</p><ul>\n<li>No matter what your opponent takes (1 to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span> stones)</li>\n<li>You can take enough to make the total removed equal to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>This keeps you in control until the final move</li>\n</ul><h3 class=\"markdown-h2\">Example: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k = 3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span> (can take 1, 2, or 3)</h3><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m = 4</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span></span></span></span>. Losing positions: 0, 4, 8, 12, 16, ...</p><p>Starting with 15 stones:</p><ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>15</mn><mtext> </mtext><mo lspace=\"0.22em\" rspace=\"0.22em\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mo><mtext> </mtext><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">15 \\bmod 4 = 3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">15</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">mod</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span>, so first player wins by taking 3 stones</li>\n<li>Leaves 12 stones (multiple of 4) for opponent</li>\n<li>Whatever opponent takes, you take to total 4</li>\n<li>You control the game until you take the last stone</li>\n</ul><p>Starting with 16 stones:</p><ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>16</mn><mtext> </mtext><mo lspace=\"0.22em\" rspace=\"0.22em\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mo><mtext> </mtext><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">16 \\bmod 4 = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">16</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">mod</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span>, so first player is in a losing position</li>\n<li>Any move you make leaves <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(16-1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">16</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(16-2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">16</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(16-3)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">16</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> stones</li>\n<li>All of these have non-zero remainders mod 4</li>\n<li>Your opponent can then force you into a losing position</li>\n</ul><p>Want to explore more? Continue to <strong>Nim Game: Variations</strong> to learn about multi-pile Nim and the Sprague-Grundy theorem.</p></div></details>","rawContent","\n# The General Problem\n\nYou're playing Nim with these rules:\n- Start with $n$ stones in a pile\n- Players alternate turns\n- On your turn, you must remove 1, 2, ..., or $k$ stones (where $k$ is the maximum)\n- The player who takes the last stone wins\n\n# The Question\n\nFor any values of $n$ (starting stones) and $k$ (maximum take), can you determine:\n1. Whether the first player can guarantee a win?\n2. If so, what should their first move be?\n\n:::hint\nThink about the pattern you discovered in the basic version. How does it generalize?\n:::\n\n:::hint[Modular Arithmetic]\nThe key involves the remainder when dividing $n$ by $(k+1)$.\n:::\n\n:::solution\n**Answer**: The first player can win if and only if $n$ is not divisible by $(k+1)$.\n\n## The Winning Strategy\n\nLet $m = k + 1$ (one more than the maximum take).\n\n**Winning positions**: Any number of stones where $n \\bmod m \\neq 0$\n\n**Losing positions**: Any number of stones where $n \\bmod m = 0$\n\n**The Strategy**:\n1. If $n \\bmod m = 0$, you're in a losing position (your opponent can win with perfect play)\n2. If $n \\bmod m = r$ (where $0 < r \\leq k$), take $r$ stones to leave a multiple of $m$ for your opponent\n3. After each opponent move, always take enough stones to keep the total removed equal to $m$\n\n## Why This Works\n\nWhen you leave a multiple of $m$ stones:\n- No matter what your opponent takes (1 to $k$ stones)\n- You can take enough to make the total removed equal to $m$\n- This keeps you in control until the final move\n\n## Example: $k = 3$ (can take 1, 2, or 3)\n\n$m = 4$. Losing positions: 0, 4, 8, 12, 16, ...\n\nStarting with 15 stones:\n- $15 \\bmod 4 = 3$, so first player wins by taking 3 stones\n- Leaves 12 stones (multiple of 4) for opponent\n- Whatever opponent takes, you take to total 4\n- You control the game until you take the last stone\n\nStarting with 16 stones:\n- $16 \\bmod 4 = 0$, so first player is in a losing position\n- Any move you make leaves $(16-1)$, $(16-2)$, or $(16-3)$ stones\n- All of these have non-zero remainders mod 4\n- Your opponent can then force you into a losing position\n\nWant to explore more? Continue to **Nim Game: Variations** to learn about multi-pile Nim and the Sprague-Grundy theorem.\n:::\n","dynamicBlocks",[]]
